                        <p class="mt-2">We present a novel application of 3D Gaussian Splatting (3DGS) for the large-scale archival of thousands of temples in Bali. Our project, the Bali Digital Heritage Initiative, adopts a participatory approach in which local communities collect video footage of these vulnerable temples, which we transform into 3DGS scenes to serve as digital archives.</p>
